# Python Quality Toolchain

## Tool Responsibilities
- **ruff**: Linting + formatting (replaces flake8, black, isort)
- **mypy**: Static type checking
- **pytest-cov**: Test execution + coverage (threshold: 80%)
- **mutmut**: Mutation testing (run only at milestones, very slow)

## Commands Reference
- `ruff check . --fix && ruff format .`  → lint and auto-fix
- `mypy src/`                             → type check
- `pytest --cov=src --cov-fail-under=80` → test with coverage
- `mutmut run && mutmut results`         → mutation test (milestone only)

## When AI Should Remind User to Run
- Before creating a PR or pushing to main
- After significant logic changes
- Never automatically during iterative code generation